&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term post for 12 months due to funding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mental Health Services in Llanelli are looking for motivated and enthusiastic Health Care Support Workers to join the inpatient team on the Acute inpatient ward.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you enjoy the challenge of working in a busy environment we would like to hear from you. Successful applicants will work as part of a multi-disciplinary team but must be able to work flexibly and within a shift system providing 24 hour a day cover, 365 days a year.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Staff are provided with a supportive working environment and the opportunity for professional development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh and have the ability to travel between sites in a timely manner are desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on the 20th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDaniel JonesJob titleInterim Ward ManagerEmail addressdaniel.jones8@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01554 745752&lt;/p&gt;
